== International work ==
In 1987, Farmer, along with [[Ophelia Dahl]], [[Jim Yong Kim]], Thomas J. White and Todd McCormack, co-founded [[Partners In Health]]. PIH began in [[Cange, Haiti|Cange]] in the Central Plateau of [[Haiti]] and has developed into a worldwide health organization. [[Zanmi Lasante|The PIH hospital in Haiti]] provides free treatment to patients. PIH helps patients living in poverty to obtain effective drugs to treat [[tuberculosis]] and [[AIDS]].

In addition to his hospital in Haiti, Farmer oversees projects in [[Russia]], [[Rwanda]], [[Lesotho]], [[Malawi]] and [[Peru]]. His approach has its basis in ethnographic analysis and real world practicality.<ref name="ProfileUM">{{cite web | accessdate = 2007-07-01
| url = http://www.jayweisscenter.org/x64.xml
| title = Paul Farmer, MD, PhD
| publisher = The Jay Weiss Center for Social Medicine and Health Equity, University of Miami Leonard M. Miller School of Medicine | archiveurl = http://web.archive.org/web/20070721070317/http://www.jayweisscenter.org/x64.xml <!-- Bot retrieved archive --> | archivedate = 2007-07-21}}</ref>

[[Mountains Beyond Mountains|''Mountains Beyond Mountains: The Quest of Dr. Paul Farmer, a Man Who Would Cure the World']] by [[Tracy Kidder]] details Farmer's work in Haiti, Peru, and Russia, as well as his efforts to balance clinical and academic responsibilities with having a family of his own. The book narrates the interactions and conflicts Farmer faces as he attempts to secure healthcare for the poor in Haiti.

Paul Farmer sits on the board of the Aristide Foundation for democracy and is a co-founder and Board Member of the [[Institute for Justice & Democracy in Haiti]].<ref>[http://www.ijdh.org/board.htm ]{{dead link|date=March 2011}}</ref> He is also a member of the Advisory Board of Incentives for Global Health, the NGO focused on developing the [[Health Impact Fund]].{{Citation needed|date=May 2010}}

Farmer was appointed as the Deputy UN Special Envoy for Haiti, by former US President Bill Clinton, UN Special Envoy for Haiti, on August 11, 2009.{{Citation needed|date=May 2010}} In this role, Dr. Farmer will support Clinton and assist in advancing their work on a day-to-day basis.{{Citation needed|date=May 2010}}

Farmer is a board member of [[Kageno]] Worldwide, Inc., a community development agency that has worked in Kenya and Rwanda.

